http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Central-govt.-sanctions-new-posts/article14002719.ece

Chief Minister Oommen Chandy on Saturday said the Central government had sanctioned nine posts of additional judges in the Kerala High Court.He was speaking at the foundation-stone-laying ceremony of the Bar Council of Kerala’s M.K. Nambyar Academy for Continuing Legal Education.With the sanctioning of nine more posts of judges, the total sanctioned strength of the judges has gone up to 47. At present, the working strength of High Court judges is 35.The Chief Minister said that it had been decided to increase the contribution for the Lawyers Welfare Fund from Rs.5 lakh to Rs 10 lakh.— Special Correspondent